The Finedon Church Sunday School Entertainment Society was formed in 1898 and the first pantomime performed in 1937 was Aladdin. A pantomime is now performed annually in the Star Hall where all productions have been staged.Finedon has a wealth of comic talent much appreciated by local audiences.
{The Butterfly.}
It is usual for a hibernating butterfly to appear during the run of the show.If it appears the show is usually a success.One year someone trod on the butterfly and one of the principals fell down some steps and broke her ankle.She finished the week on crutches.
